{"questionId":"12594","questionHtml":"<p>Write down an expression for the width of the garden in terms of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"> <mi>x</mi> </math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x - 4.5\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mn>4.5</mn> </math></span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1) (C1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"w = x - 4.5\"> <mi>w</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mn>4.5</mn> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; width<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = x - 4.5\"> <mo>=</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mn>4.5</mn> </math></span>.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12594","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ2.T_7a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Write down an expression for the width of the garden in terms of x .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Prior learning"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}